              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Potential LDAP injection"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In Python, LDAP Injection (CWE-90) occurs when untrusted input is used in LDAP filters or DNs,\nallowing attackers to modify queries or access unauthorized data.\n\nFor example (vulnerable):\n```python\nfilter_str = f\"(\u0026(uid={username})(objectClass=user))\"\nconn.search_s(base_dn, ldap.SCOPE_SUBTREE, filter_str)\n```\n\n## How to remediate:\n- Use ldap.filter.escape_filter_chars() to escape input.\n- Validate input with regex or allowlists.\n- Use parameterized queries where available."
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "DATADOG_RULE_TYPE:datadog-ai-static-analyzer",
                  "CWE:90",
                  "SEVERITY:WARNING",
