              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE:HIGH",
              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:The 'rememberMeKey', used as an authentication token in an HTTP cookie and session store, is generated using `math/rand.NormFloat64()`. The `math/rand` package produces cryptographically weak, pseudo-random numbers, especially when seeded with `time.Now().UnixNano()` (line 20). This makes the 'rememberMeKey' predictable and vulnerable to brute-force attacks, allowing an attacker to guess valid session tokens and potentially hijack user sessions. This is a direct violation of CWE-330 (Weak Randomness) as a security-sensitive token relies on a non-cryptographically secure random source."
